record_data.record_plain_text: CRAVEN COUNTY WOOD ENERGY LIMITED PARTNERSHIP FERC SCHEDULE NO. 1 ELECTRIC TARIFF 1. Availability: Craven County Wood Energy Limited Partnership ("Craven” or “Seller") makes electric energy, capacity and other products listed below in Paragraph 4 under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale at market-based rates. 2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to (i) all sales for resale of energy, capacity; and (ii) certain ancillary services described in Paragraph 6. 3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Craven. 4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Craven. 5. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Craven shall comply with the provision of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller’s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller’s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller’s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. Ancillary Services: RTO/ISO Specific: PJM Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM interconnection, L.L.C. (“PJM”) and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. 7. Limitation and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: The following waivers of the Commission’s Regulation were granted per FERD Letter Order dated December 2, 2005 in Dockets Nos. ER05-1489-000 and ER05-1489-001, at pages 3-4: (1) Subparts B and C of Part 35, regarding the filing of rate schedules, except for Sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 (which requires applicant to file a Notice of Cancellation or Termination when it ceases its marketing activities), and 35.16 (which requires applicant to file a notice of succession whenever its name or operational control is changed). (2) Part 101, regarding the uniform system of accounts; and Part 141, regarding statements and reports, with the exception of 18 C.F.R. Section 141.14, and 141.15 (1999). Notwithstanding the waiver of the accounting and reporting here, Craven is expected to keep its accounting records in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles. Blanket approval under Section 204 of the FPA and Part 34 of the Commission’s regulations for all future issuances of securities and assumption of liability. 8. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).

record_data.record_title: Craven County Wood Energy LP FERC Sched No 1 Elec Tariff
record_data.record_plain_text:
? FERC SCHEDULE NO. 1 ELECTRIC TARIFF
1. Availability: Seller makes electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services available under this tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited below.
2. Applicability: This tariff is applicable to all wholesale sales of energy, capacity, and ancillary services by Seller not otherwise subject to a particular tariff of Seller.
3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller.
4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller.
5. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provision of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller’s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller’s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller’s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
6. Ancillary Services:
MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. (“MISO”) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO.
PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM interconnection, L.L.C. (“PJM”) and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection.
New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc. New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc. California: Seller offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation ("CAISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO. Southwest Power Pool: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (“SPP”) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP. Third-party ancillary services: Seller offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve Supplemental and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) Sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e. where the entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) Sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider’s OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.
7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Seller has received waiver of: Subparts B and C of Part 35, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; Part 41, Part 101, with the exception that waiver of the provisions that apply to hydropower licensees has not been granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects, Part 141, exceptsection 141.15; and received blanket approval under Part 34. Craven County Wood Energy Limited Partnership, Docket Nos. ER05-1489-000 and ER05-1489-001 (2005)(unpublished letter order).
8. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 1 seller in all regions, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
